"v.道歉；辩解 【英】 v. 道歉(say one is sorry ) 【考】 apologize : contrite / compliment : impressed(道歉表达后悔/称赞 表达被打动) 【记】 apo(远离)+log(说话) +ize →离(别人)远一点说 话→不面对面骂→道歉 v. 道歉; 辩解 【例】I must apologize for calling you so late 实在抱歉, 这么晚给您打电话. apologize to sb 向某人道歉apologize for oneself 为自已解辩或辩护 【记】apo远离, log说话－远一点说话－因为作错事理亏－道歉 【类】apologize: contrite = compliment: impressed道歉表达后悔 = 称赞表达被打动 【记】apology 道歉 apologize (v.)  1590s, ""to speak in defense of;"" see apology + -ize. Main modern sense ""to regretfully acknowledge"" is attested by 1725. The Greek equivalent, apologizesthai, meant simply ""to give an account."" Related: Apologized; apologizing."
